  <h1>The Brown Bear</h1> <!-- header of body of text -->
  	<!-- below is beginning of paragraph -->
  	<p>The brown bear (Ursus arctos) is native to parts of northern Eurasia and North America. Its conservation status is currently "Least Concern." There are many subspecies within the brown bear species, including the Atlas bear and the Himalayan brown bear.
  	</p>
  <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brown_bear" target="_blank">Learn More</a> <!-- creates link /image that opens in new web page -->
  	<p>The following are subspecies of bears:
  	</p>
  		<ul> <!-- unordered list of items -->
    		<li>Arctos</li> <!-- the unordered items -->
    		<li>Collarus</li>
    		<li>Horribilis</li>
    		<li>Nelsoni (extinct)</li>
  		</ul>
  	<p>The following countries have the largest populations<br /> of brown bears:</p>
